      "writtenOn": "2020-11-23T22:09:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Also, sharding needs to be intentional and well documented, for example between LF, CRLF or CR only.  CR only can happen for tool that tries to replace the current line, like when you run ninja locally.\n\nIs the assumption that the shard id is monotonically increasing and starts at 0? Write it in the description.",
      "parentUuid": "bed2460b_1472d820",
      "revId": "f1489c97e28ff624b8375b814728266df751f231",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "30ac53b1_bcd3c121",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/bq/artifact_row.proto",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 39,
      "author": {
        "id": 1157909
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-23T22:31:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027d think we can shard when see a line break (regardless of LF, CRLF or CR), unless you have a strong preference on one type of line breaks.",
      "parentUuid": "4b4f820a_13c90b7f",
      "revId": "f1489c97e28ff624b8375b814728266df751f231",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b3b30908_39d0d78e",
