        "id": 1000487
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-24T01:09:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It needs to be consistent, for example you can\u0027t split on CR if a LF follows. That\u0027s generally the case on Windows, but not other OSes. So I prefer this to be decided up front and explicitly written in the proto as it\u0027ll be painful to change later.\n\nI think this can be encoded as r\u0027(\\r\\n?|\\n)\u0027 or r\u0027(\\r\\n|\\r|\\n)\u0027",
      "parentUuid": "30ac53b1_bcd3c121",
      "revId": "f1489c97e28ff624b8375b814728266df751f231",
